# 999 bug (without manually fixing this, X will not start)

After lh_chroot or after a `lh build` and a `sudo lh clean --binary` you need to fix the odd permissions that result:

	x61:~/webc/config-webc/mini% sudo chroot chroot /bin/bash
	root@x61:/# cd /home/webc
	root@x61:/home/webc# ls -lah
	total 24K
	drwxr-xr-x 2  999  999 4.0K Jun  8 16:27 .
	drwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4.0K Jun  8 16:27 ..
	-rw-r--r-- 1  999  999  220 Jun  8 16:27 .bash_logout
	-rw-r--r-- 1  999  999  560 May 28 19:53 .bash_profile
	-rw-r--r-- 1  999  999 2.2K Jun  8 16:27 .bashrc
	-rw-r--r-- 1  999  999 2.9K Jun  4 16:33 .xsession

**Work around** by manually fixing the permission:

	root@x61:/home/webc# chown -R webc:webc ~webc
	root@x61:/home/webc# ls -lah
	total 24K
	drwxr-xr-x 2 webc webc 4.0K Jun  8 16:27 .
	drwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4.0K Jun  8 16:27 ..
	-rw-r--r-- 1 webc webc  220 Jun  8 16:27 .bash_logout
	-rw-r--r-- 1 webc webc  560 May 28 19:53 .bash_profile
	-rw-r--r-- 1 webc webc 2.2K Jun  8 16:27 .bashrc
	-rw-r--r-- 1 webc webc 2.9K Jun  4 16:33 .xsession
	root@x61:/home/webc#

Then `exit` and `lh binary` to finalise the build.

I've tried [hooking in a permission fixing
script](http://git.debian.org/?p=debian-live/config-webc.git;a=blob;f=mini/config/chroot_local-hooks/perms),
however it does not seem to work. :/ Seemingly after the script is run the
UID/GID will change to 999!

